Constructor():
!. Construct is a special type of method that is automatically called when an instance of a class is created
2. its primary job is to initialize the newly created object
3. constructors have the same name as the class and may or may not accept parameters.

Default Constructor:
1. Default constructor doesnt accept any parameters
2. If we dont define any constructors in the class, c# provides a default constructor automatically
3. it initiazes member variables to their default values i.e null for reference types, zero for numeric types.

